text: Thomas Trenchard (1672–1703), of Wolveton, Charminster, Dorset, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Dorchester in 1689, 17 December 1690 and February 1701. He represented Wareham in 1695 and 1698, and Dorset in December 1701.http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1660-1690/member/trenchard- thomas-ii-1672-1703 ==References== Category:1672 births Category:1703 deaths Category:English MPs 1689–1690 Category:People from Dorset Category:English MPs 1701 Category:Members of the Parliament of England for Dorchester Category:English MPs 1695–1698 Category:English MPs 1701–1702
